    "point_1": {
      "type": "Text",
      "props": {
        "text": "1/ someone reported a hardcoded Neo4j password in a public GitHub issue. not a security advisory. a public issue. MiroShark had no private channel for disclosure. PR #158 fixes that.",
        "variant": "body"
      }
    },
    "point_2": {
      "type": "Text",
      "props": {
        "text": "2/ 1,268 stars. three production integrators — RevaultDrops, AntFleet, Capacitr — running it as AI infrastructure. AGPL licensed. and until today: no responsible disclosure policy. issue #88 appeared as a public GitHub issue because there was nowhere else to send it.",
        "variant": "body"
      }
    },
    "point_3": {
      "type": "Text",
      "props": {
        "text": "3/ PR #158: SECURITY.md adds a private email channel and a 90-day coordinated disclosure window. researchers can report without going public immediately. maintainers get time to patch before a CVE lands cold.",
        "variant": "body"
      }
    },
    "point_4": {
      "type": "Text",
      "props": {
        "text": "4/ three teams depending on MiroShark as infrastructure means the attack surface isn't just the repo — it's their production systems. SECURITY.md is table stakes. next hardcoded credential gets a 90-day fix window, not a public thread.",
        "variant": "body"
      }
    },
